author: 404 not pound
text: 880th comment, maybe the right time. I am from New Delhi, pollution in Delhi NCR has always been between 125-225, bad to worse, throughout the year. Causes? many = coal burning, msw burning, vehicles, unchecked polluting industries, bad roads, no vacuum cleaning of roads (do it at least four times a month), open field with almost no grass. During this time of the year (October to January), when there is very little movement of air (breeze) farmers in the neighboring state starts burning their leftover stubbles (fast way to get rid of the leftovers and cheap), now, there is already not much breeze blowing and you add more pollution to the air which then stays locked in the atmosphere and causes smog. There are WAYS to get rid of air pollution and no it's not expensive. You need to pass a few strict laws and maybe spend a little on a few pieces of equipment.
